    "summary": "Maurin H\u00f6rler is a consultant at DNV within the department of Energy Market and Strategy based in Arnhem, the Netherlands. He holds a MSc in Energy and Environmental Science from the University of Groningen (RUG) with a focus on energy systems, scenario analysis and energy modelling.\n\nMaurin has a passion for renewable energy along with a general interest in sustainable development. He believes it is key to smartly integrate more carbon-free energy technologies into the current and future energy market while simultaneously decarbonize hard-to-abate sectors via electrification, to successfully push the energy transition forward. Maurin has a comprehensive knowledge of qualitative and quantitative assessments regarding the operation and control of power systems and energy markets with focus on Europe. In his two graduation research projects he analysed the energy performance of space heating technologies within the residential sector as well as examined the power variabilities among various time-cycles of future international energy markets by creating a novel methodology.",
