                    "description": "Maurin is a consultant at DNV within the department of Energy Markets and Strategy based in Arnhem, the Netherlands. Maurin is part of the Power Markets & Systems section with a focus on market valuation and market integration studies. He is involved in projects which require experience in energy market modeling, balancing market & frequency control modeling, congestion management analysis and resource adequacy. Thereby, it is key to have a profound understanding of energy policies & regulatory frameworks, in developing potential future scenarios and in evaluating the impact of renewable capacity expansion on the power grid network. Outcomes of such studies facilitate the decision-making process of customers by gaining a better insight into future price formations (power price forecasts), future reliabilities of power systems, and the dynamics of current and future energy markets.",
